19/09/2005
RUSE, Bulgaria -- The National Service for Organised Crime Fighting (NSOCF) has stopped an apparent attempt to illegally traffic a substance of possible dual use via the country's territory, NSOCF Chief General Valentin Petrov announced at a news conference Monday (19 September). He said that an operation in the northern city of Ruse resulted in the confiscation of 3kg of the rare metal Hafnium, which can be used for radioactive synthesis. The material was found in a car bound from Bulgaria to Romania. One person faces criminal charges. (bTV, Dnevnik - 19/09/05)
